                        </origin>
                        <provenance><p> The manuscript entered the library of Nawāb Ṣāḥib ʿAlī Khān Bahādur in 1187 A.H. (c. 1773).</p>                           
                        <p>It was later owned presumably by a French owner, who inscribed the note on folio 1a. Other former owners include 'W. Chatfield' (possibly <persName>William Chatfield (1815-1902)</persName>) and <persName>Samuel Hawtayne Lewin (1795-1840)</persName> in 1823. </p>
                            <!-- Bland -->
                            <p>Formerly part of the collection of the Persian scholar <persName
                                    type="standard"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/#Bland,_Nathaniel,_1803-1865"
                                    >Nathaniel Bland (1803-1865)</persName>. Bland’s oriental
                                manuscripts were sold through Bernard Quaritch in 1866 to <persName
                                    type="standard"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/#Crawford,_Alexander_Crawford_Lindsay,_Earl_of,_1812-1880"
                                    >Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford</persName>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
